"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-02-Who-will-make-headlines-on-August-2-at-Paris-Olympics--1vJKWpRXtsI-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Sports Scene  Copied  A total of 25 gold medals are up for grabs on Friday at the 2024 Paris Summer Olympics.  China's Zheng Siwei and Huang Yaqiong will face South Korea's Kim Won-Ho and Jeong Na-Eun in badminton's mixed doubles gold medal match at 15:00 (GMT+2) on later Friday.  In tennis, China's Zhang Zhizhen and Wang Xinyu will look to claim China's first mixed doubles gold at the Olympics at 19:00 (GMT+2).  And Chinese swimmer Wang Shun will compete in the men's 200-meter individual medley final at 20:43 (GMT+2), while the BMX cycling men's final will start at 21:35 (GMT+2), followed by the women's final.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"